r!\") \" accepts a string or symbol event name and returns the installed callback value so it can be removed later.\") (li (code \"websocket-remove-event-listener!\") \" accepts either the original listener procedure or the returned callback value.\")) (h3 (@ (id \"23-common-setup-helpers\")) \"2.3 Common Setup Helpers\") (pre (code \"(include-lib websocket)\\n\\n(define ws (websocket-new \\\"wss://example.invalid/socket\\\" (vector \\\"chat\\\")))\\n(define mock-ws (js-eval \\\"globalThis.WebSocket\\\"))\\n(define send-data \\\"hello\\\")\")) (h3 (@ (id \"24-environment-and-availability-notes\")) \"2.4 Environment and Availability Notes\") (ul (li \"These bindings are browser-oriented and assume a \" (code \"WebSocket\") \" implementation is available.\") (li \"In browsers that do not expose \" (code \"WebSocket\") \", construction will fail.\") (li \"In tests, it is often easier to install a mock constructor on \" (code \"globalThis.WebSocket\") \" before calling \" (code \"js-websocket-new\") \".\")) (h3 (@ (id \"25-public-wrapper-layer\")) \"2.5 Public Wrapper Layer\") (p \"The checked wrapper layer is intended for application code and examples.\") (pre (code \"(include-lib websocket)\\n\\n(define ws (websocket-new \\\"wss://example.invalid/socket\\\" (vector \\\"chat\\\")))\\n(websocket-onopen! ws (lambda (_evt) (void)))\\n(websocket-onmessage! ws (lambda (_evt) (void)))\\n(websocket-onclose! ws (lambda (_evt) (void)))\\n(websocket-onerror! ws (lambda (_evt) (void)))\\n(websocket-add-event-listener! ws 'message (lambda (_evt) (void)))\")) (p \"The wrapper exports the following checked helpers:\") (ul (li (code \"websocket?\")) (li (code \"check-websocket\")) (li (code \"websocket-new\")) (li (code \"websocket-send\")) (li (code \"websocket-close\")) (li (code \"websocket-url\")) (li (code \"websocket-ready-state\")) (li (code \"websocket-buffered-amount\")) (li (code \"websocket-protocol\")) (li (code \"websocket-extensions\")) (li (code \"websocket-onopen!\"))